Biden: The Democratic Convention May Need To Be A Virtual Event This YearEnlarge this image toggle caption Biden for President via AP Biden for President via APFormer Vice President Joe Biden says the Democratic National Convention may need take place virtually as a result of the deepening coronavirus outbreak.
"We may have to do a virtual convention," Biden said on ABC's This Week.
In delaying the convention, its organizers said they would explore further options to maintain public health, including adjusting the convention's format, crowd size and schedule.
"He may not like how he looks in a mask," Biden said of the president, saying it is a matter of following science.
"I was basically apologizing and making it clear I wasn't trying to be presumptuous, in any way push him," Biden said.